The paper deals with upper bounds on code sizes for permutation codes using the Kendall tau distance metric. This falls under the realm of information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of coherent configurations and semidefinite programming also suggests a connection to linear algebra and optimization (cs.LG, cs.SD). Finally, the mention of association scheme theory and Delsarte's approach points towards the study of algebraic structures (cs.CC).
